<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Caitlyn Jenner set world records as an Olympic decathlete in the 70s. </p>

<p>And the 70-year-old still looked like a super-sport while teeing off at the Lake Sherwood Country Club in Thousand Oaks, California on Monday.</p>

<p>The Secrets Of My Life author kept things classic for golfing, rocking a preppy all white ensemble for her afternoon at the driving range.</p>

<p>Swing time: Caitlyn Jenner wore all white as she enjoyed a day of golfing at  Lake Sherwood Country Club in Thousand Oaks, California on Monday</p>

<p>Caitlyn looked leggy in an ivory skort that she teamed with a snug polo top.</p>

<p>Keeping Southern California's late summer heat at bay, the skin cancer survivor topped off her outfit with a fishing hat with a neck flap to protect from sunburns.</p>

<p>Before practicing her swing Jenner decided got ready for the day with some coffee, seen picking up a cold, sugary drink from her local Starbucks.</p>

<p>The retired reality star opted against a face mask at both locations.</p>

<p>Treat yourself: Before practicing her swing Jenner decided got ready for the day with some coffee, seen picking up a cold, sugary drink from her local Starbucks</p>

<p>Last week, Caitlyn chimed in after news broke previously of the impending conclusion to E!'s reality phenomenon Keeping Up With The Kardashians.</p>

<p>The father of Kendall and Kylie Jenner, who herself had been on the show, reflected in an Instagram video and on her new YouTube channel that she is 'sad' to see the show go, a program which covered 'a great time' in her life. </p>

<p>She has appeared in over 150 episodes of the show focusing on his blended family with ex-wife Kris, from 2007 up until their divorce in 2015 and subsequent gender transition. </p>

<p>She went on to star for two seasons on the E! spin-off I Am Cait in 2016. </p>

<p>Last week: Caitlyn chimed in after news broke previously of the impending conclusion to E!'s reality phenomenon Keeping Up With The Kardashians</p>

<p>Reality history: Jenner reflected in an Instagram video and on her new YouTube channel that she is 'sad' to see the show go, a program which covered 'a great time' in her life</p>

<p>Caitlyn revealed in an interview with an Australian TV show that she had not been given advance notice that Keeping Up With The Kardashians would be coming to an end after 14 years and 20 seasons.</p>

<p>She told Australia's The Morning Show that she found out about the end of KUWTK on the news like everyone else.</p>

<p>'Nobody called me, I heard it through the media. Was I surprised? No,' she added.</p>

<p>She then praised her ex-wife Kris Jenner and their family, saying: 'That show, it's probably the greatest reality show in history. There are over 500 episodes over 14 years.'</p>

<p>Caitlyn went on to declare: 'The girls and Kris have have done just an amazing job with the show and keeping it going for this long. But everybody is in a different place now and I think it's time to move on. But what a run.'</p>

<p>Didn't know: She also revealed in an interview that she had not been given advance notice that Keeping Up With The Kardashians would be coming to an end after 14 years and 20 seasons</p>
